public function call(string $method, string $uri = '', array $options = []): ApiResponseInterface
{
    // 1. Set hash key from parameters
    $this->apiToken->setHashKey($this->getParameters());

    // 2. Check if valid token exists; if not, login
    if (!$this->apiToken->hasValidToken()) {
        $this->login();  // Line 94
    }

    // 3. Make authenticated call
    $apiResponse = $this->authenticatedCall($method, $uri, $options);

    // 4. If success, return response
    if (!$apiResponse instanceof ApiResponseErrorInterface) {
        return $apiResponse;
    }

    // 5. If error but NOT token error, throw exception
    $errorMessage = $apiResponse->getErrorMesssage();
    if (!$this->tokenError->isInvalidToken($apiResponse)) {
        // Line 106-110: Throw ApiClientException (4xx) or ApiRetryableException (5xx)
    }

    // 6. If 401/token error: re-login and retry once
    $this->logger->debug(sprintf('New token required ! %s', $errorMessage));
    $this->login();
    return $this->authenticatedCall($method, $uri, $options);
}
```

**Login Method (Lines 130-162):**
```php
private function login(): void
{
    // Get parameters (all required with throwError=true)
    $loginUri = $this->getStringParameter('login_uri', true);
    $loginMultiTenantHeaderKey = $this->getStringParameter('login_multi_tenant_header_key');
    $credentials = $this->getArrayParameter('credentials', true);
    $responseTokenKey = $this->getStringParameter('response_token_key') ?? 'token';
    $loginDataKey = $this->getStringParameter('login_data_key') ?? 'json';

    // Build options
    $options = [$loginDataKey => $credentials];

    // Optional: Multi-tenant header
    if ($loginMultiTenantHeaderKey) {
        $headerValue = str_ends_with(strtolower($loginMultiTenantHeaderKey), '-id')
            ? $this->identityService->getCurrentWebinstance()->getId()
            : $this->identityService->getCurrentWebinstance()->getShortname();
        $options['headers'][$loginMultiTenantHeaderKey] = $headerValue;
    }

    // Call login endpoint (Line 147)
    $apiResponse = $this->apiClient->call('POST', $loginUri, $options);

    // Extract token (Line 154)
    if (!\is_string($newToken = $apiResponse->getValue($responseTokenKey))) {
        throw new ApiTokenException(...);
    }

    // Store token (Line 161)
    $this->apiToken->setToken($newToken);
}
```

**Hashing & Parameters:**
- Line 92: `$this->apiToken->setHashKey($this->getParameters());`
- Credentials (except password) + URI used as discriminant (see TokenCacheKey.php lines 57-77)

**Token Invalid Detection (Line 105):**
- `$this->tokenError->isInvalidToken($apiResponse)` → Delegate to TokenErrorInterface implementation

