## 7. COMPLETE AUTH FLOW LIFECYCLE

### Scenario: First Request with JWT Auth

```
[Initial State]
├─ Token not cached (first time or expired)
└─ No HTTP Client yet

[Call Sequence]
1. User calls: $authJwtApiClient->call('GET', '/contacts', [])
   └─ AuthJwtApiClient::call() (Line 90)

2. Set hash key from parameters
   └─ $this->apiToken->setHashKey($this->getParameters())  (Line 92)
   └─ TokenCacheKey::getDiscriminant()
      ├─ Extract credentials (except password)
      ├─ Extract discriminant_uri/base_uri/main_uri
      └─ Return array: ['username' => 'user', 'uri' => 'https://api.example.com']
   └─ CacheUtils::computeKey() → MD5 hash

3. Check if valid token exists
   └─ $this->apiToken->hasValidToken()  (Line 93)
   └─ RedisApiToken::hasValidToken()
      └─ RedisApiToken::getToken()
         ├─ cache.get(hashKey) → null (first time)
         └─ return null

4. NOT valid → LOGIN REQUIRED
   └─ $this->login()  (Line 94)
   └─ AuthJwtApiClient::login() (Line 130)
      ├─ Get parameters:
      │  ├─ login_uri: 'https://api.ingenie.fr/login'
      │  ├─ credentials: {'email': 'user@example.com', 'password': 'secret'}
      │  ├─ response_token_key: 'token'
      │  └─ login_data_key: 'json'
      │
      ├─ Build options: {'json': credentials, 'headers': {...}}
      │
      ├─ Call login endpoint
      │  └─ $this->apiClient->call('POST', login_uri, options)
      │  └─ BaseApiClient::call() (Line 57 of BaseApiClient)
      │     ├─ $client->request('POST', url, options)
      │     ├─ If 2xx/3xx: return ApiResponse(code, data, url)
      │     └─ If 4xx/5xx: return ApiResponseError(code, data, url)
      │
      ├─ Extract token from response
      │  ├─ newToken = response.getValue('token')  (Line 154)
      │  └─ If not string: throw ApiTokenException
      │
      └─ Store token in Redis
         └─ $this->apiToken->setToken(newToken)  (Line 161)
         └─ RedisApiToken::setToken()
            ├─ Verify hashKey is set (line 40)
            ├─ Decode JWT:
            │  ├─ JwtToken::set(token)
            │  ├─ JWTHelper::decodeToken(token) → ['exp' => 1234567890]
            │  └─ Store expirationTime = 1234567890
            │
            ├─ Compute TTL:
            │  └─ getTtl() = exp - time()  (Line 68 of JwtToken)
            │     Example: 1234567890 - 1234567000 = 890 seconds
            │
            └─ Cache in Redis:
               └─ cache.set(hashKey, token, 890)  (Line 47)
               └─ After 890 seconds, Redis auto-expires key
               └─ Log: "Token store into redis cache"

5. Make authenticated call
   └─ $this->authenticatedCall('GET', '/contacts', [])  (Line 97)
   └─ AuthJwtApiClient::authenticatedCall() (Line 175)
      ├─ callUri = main_uri + uri = 'https://api.example.com' + '/contacts'
      ├─ Get token from Redis
      │  └─ token = $this->apiToken->getToken()
      │     ├─ RedisApiToken::getToken()
      │     ├─ cachedToken = cache.get(hashKey)  (Line 69)
      │     ├─ Check isExpired() (Line 74)
      │     └─ return token or null
      │
      ├─ Add auth header
      │  └─ options['auth_bearer'] = token  (Line 185)
      │  └─ (or custom key from 'client_auth_key' parameter)
      │
      └─ Make HTTP call
         └─ $this->apiClient->call('GET', url, options)
         └─ BaseApiClient::call()
            └─ $client->request('GET', url, options)
            └─ Response: ApiResponse(200, data, url) ✓ SUCCESS

6. Return response to user
   └─ return $apiResponse  (Line 101)
```

### Scenario: Token Expired / 401 Response

```
[Cached token, but server returns 401]

1. User calls: $authJwtApiClient->call('GET', '/contacts', [])

2. Check token
   └─ hasValidToken() → true (TTL still > 10 seconds)
   └─ Token exists in Redis

3. Make authenticated call
   └─ authenticatedCall() → ApiResponseError(401, error_data, url)

4. Check error response
   └─ if (!$apiResponse instanceof ApiResponseErrorInterface) { return; }  (Line 100)
   └─ IS error → continue

5. Check if token error
   └─ $this->tokenError->isInvalidToken($apiResponse)  (Line 105)
   └─ TokenErrorInterface implementations:
      ├─ StatusCodeTokenError: 401 === code
      ├─ ApiPlatformTokenError: 401 === code && message in ['Invalid JWT Token', 'Expired JWT Token']
      └─ ApiIngenieTokenError: 401 === code && error in ['invalid_token', 'token_expired']

6. IS token error → RE-LOGIN AND RETRY
   └─ $this->logger->debug('New token required !...')  (Line 113)
   └─ $this->login()  (Line 114)
      └─ Repeat login flow (steps 4 of first scenario)
      └─ New token stored in Redis, overwriting old one

   └─ return $this->authenticatedCall($method, $uri, $options)  (Line 116)
      └─ New HTTP call with fresh token
      └─ Should succeed now
```

### Scenario: Non-Token Error (4xx / 5xx)

```
[Other errors like 404, 500, etc.]

1. User calls: $authJwtApiClient->call('GET', '/nonexistent', [])

2. Token valid, make call
   └─ Response: ApiResponseError(404, error_data, url)

3. IS error response

4. Check if token error
   └─ isInvalidToken() → FALSE (code is 404, not 401)

5. NOT token error → THROW EXCEPTION
   └─ if (500 > $apiResponse->getCode())  (Line 106)
      └─ 404 < 500 → throw ApiClientException('...', 404)  (Line 107)

   └─ else
      └─ 500+ → throw ApiRetryableException('...', 500)  (Line 110)
```

